The task contained defects across all four Harbor authoring areas:

Format

task.toml declared artifacts as a string instead of a top-level array.
The artifact path pointed to /app/out.json, while the task actually produces /app/report.json.
allow_internet was enabled even though the task is completely offline.

Environment

The Docker base image was not pinned by digest, making builds non-reproducible.
The reference solution (solution_hint.py) was leaked into the agent environment, allowing agents to inspect the answer.

Verifier

The verifier only checked that report.json existed and was non-empty.
It did not validate the JSON contents, so incorrect outputs could receive full credit.
tests/test.sh wrote reward.txt to the wrong location and did not generate ctrf.json, which is required by Harbor.

Instructions

instruction.md was ambiguous and did not specify the required output filename, JSON schema, or exact success criteria.
The instructions were inconsistent with what the verifier should check.
